ҫThe IATP - Raising Asbestos Awareness Together
Remembering those whose lives have been affected by asbestos
The living owe it to those who can no longer speak
to tell their story for them"О
ЛA Battersea girl with a heart of gold. cared for her parents growing old
She would always give her time to share, with anyone feeling in despair
When troubles seem to fill their day, helped to clear their problems away
The world is now a sadder place, without her kind and smiling face
In memory of Mabel Gladys Coote 1922-2017"П
МBRIAN BOTTING FRICS 1932 2014
First Chairman of the Friends of Battersea Park 1990- 1999
The Hungarian Oak opposite was planted in his memory
A great servant of the Park with a mischievous sense of fun"Ф
СIn loving memory of a very special person
Gioacchino Visaggi who fell asleep on the 30 May 2016
He will be truly missed by his wife and two daughters
whom he dedicated his entire life, and all those who were
helped by his enormous generosity
He has shown to us all to never give up fighting in our
beliefs despite all the hardships"Ш
ХIn celebration of the marriage of
Dan Moss and Claudie Sellers
18th July 2015
So, she leaning on her husband's arm, they turned homeward
by a rosy path which the gracious sun struck out for them in its setting"б
ЮMarie Lindsay-Hogg 1928-2016
Artist, actress, member of Royal Brompton Hospital
Singing for Breathing group. Glorious, much-loved and
missed mother to 7, grandmother, great-grandmother and
beloved friend and neighbour."в
